(1662, 3, '2013-07-09 18:31:28', '2013-07-09 18:31:28', 'The Redemption Period, is a period after your home has already been sold at a foreclosure sale where you can still reclaim your home. In order to do this, you will need to pay the outstanding mortgage balance and all costs incurred during the foreclosure process which could be costly but may be an alternative to losing your home all together.\r\n\r\nMany states have different types of redemption periods. The redemption period and availability is often determined by whether the foreclosure is judicial or non-judicial. And, timelines and procedures can vary greatly from state to state. You can find specific information about the redemption period of your state (if applicable) by reading the state laws on foreclosure.\r\n\r\nIn this video you will learn more about what a \"redemption period\" is.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[KGVID]http://bricrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/What-is-a-housing-Redemption-Period.mp4[/KGVID]', 'What is a \"Housing Redemption Period\"?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-a-housing-redemption-period', '', '', '2013-07-09 22:19:55', '2013-07-09 22:19:55', '', 0, 'http://bricrealty.com/?p=1662', 0, 'post', '', 0),
