(1116, 1, '2013-06-08 15:55:50', '2013-06-08 15:55:50', '<a class=\"ether-frame ether-frame-1 alignright\" href=\"http://bricrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Hunters-Creek-Image.png\" rel=\"shadowbox\"><img style=\"border: 1px solid black; margin: 1px 2px;\" title=\"Hunter\'s Creek Image\" alt=\"Hunter\'s Creek Condominiums\" src=\"http://bricrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Hunters-Creek-Image.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"211\" /></a>\r\n<strong>Population:</strong>14,321\r\n<strong>Demographics:</strong>Median age is 35; 81.8 percent white, 5.18 percent black, 13.83 percent Hispanic\r\n<strong>Median household income:</strong>$67,775\r\n<strong>Schools:</strong>Hunters Creek Elementary School, Endeavor Elementary School, West Creek Elementary School, John Young Elementary School, Hunters Creek Middle School, Freedom Middle School, Freedom High School; Primrose School of Hunters Creek is for pre-kindergarten\r\n<strong>Entertainment:</strong>Turkey Trot, Holiday Concert in the Park and Craft Fair, annual Hunters Creek golf tournament, AnnualPeggy Breunig Tennis Classic Tournament\r\n\r\n<strong>Need Help Renting, Buying or Selling a Condominium or Home in Hunters Creek, FL?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Call Us Today!<strong><strong>1-800-975-1475</strong></strong></strong>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Anyone considering a move to the Orlando area should start their search for housing at Hunters Creek, a vibrant community southeast of Orlando proper that has something for just about anyone: families, singles, empty nesters, seniors, renters or owners. Much of the community was developed during the 1980s and 90s, but there are still units under construction for buyers looking for something completely new.</p>\r\nThe entire community of Hunters Creek covers 4,000 acres over which 35 different neighborhoods of single-family homes are nestled. And the home styles and prices are as varied as the owners who live there. There are villas, fairway homes and estates with water views. Apartment dwellers will find a large variety of one-, two- and three-bedroom units in seven different multi-family neighborhoods: Camden Hunters Creek, Colonial Grand at Heather Glen, Colonial Grand at Hunters Creek,the Cottages at Hunters Creek, Osprey Links, the Parks at Hunters Creek and Urbana.\r\n\r\nThe community also offers four condominium properties  Audubon Villas, Capri at Hunters Creek, Golfview and Villanova  and one townhouse development called Chartres Gardens.\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Despite its size, Hunters Creek is a cohesive community with numerous opportunities for residents to become involved and meet their neighbors through the many established clubs and social groups. For example the Hunters Creek Womens Association is involved in civic projects; and seniors will feel at home in an organization called the Fabulous 50s. Residents can volunteer to be part of Citizens on Patrol, a neighborhood watch group, or the Community Emergency Response Team.</p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Hunters Creek is an unincorporated area of Orange County, but its location could not be more optimal. Close to the Orlando International Airport and downtown Orlando, its central location also offers easy access to Floridas East Coast beaches as well as Central Floridas many entertainment attractions.</p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Plus the community has just about every amenity that someone who lives an active lifestyle might want close to home. There are seven parks located in the nearly 4-square-mile area. They range from shaded and secluded green spaces with walking paths to larger expanses that are activity-oriented with basketball, tennis and shuffleboard courts, baseball and soccer fields, fishing docks and picnic pavilions.</p>\r\nOne of the largest recreation areas, Osprey Park, has a social center where residents can play foosball, pool, table tennis, board games, video games, cards, or enjoy programs on a large-screen TV. Most of the annual community events are held at Osprey Park, many of them connected with a holiday. Hunters Creeks annual events include a Bunny in the Park spring event and a fall festival organized by the &gt;Hunters Creek Womens Association as well as a Fourth of July Celebration, Halloween Creep Nights with a haunted house and hay ride thats organized by the Hunters Creek Community Association.\r\n\r\nResidents of Hunters Creek are further served by a healthy mix of commercial spaces in and around the community. Local restaurants and drinking spots offer international cuisines to satisfy a variety of tastes. Among the best are Tijuana Flats Mexican Restaurant, Padrinos Cuban Bistro, Hunters Creek Golf Club, A Slice of New York Pizza, Millers Ale House, El Inka Grill Peruvian Restaurant and Sabana Cafe.', 'Hunter\'s Creek', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '891-revision-8', '', '', '2013-06-08 15:55:50', '2013-06-08 15:55:50', '', 891, 'http://bricrealty.com/891-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1117, 1, '2013-06-10 07:02:04', '2013-06-10 07:02:04', '<strong><a href=\"http://bricrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Lake-Mary-FL-Image.png\" rel=\"shadowbox\"><img title=\"Lake Mary, FL Image\" alt=\"Heathrow Condominiums\" src=\"http://bricrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Lake-Mary-FL-Image.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a></strong><strong>\r\nPopulation:</strong>5,896<strong>Demographics:</strong>Median age is 43; 75 percent white, 3.9 percent black, 9.8 percent Hispanic<strong>Median household income:</strong>$94,185\r\n<strong>Schools:</strong>Heathrow Elementary School (Lake Mary)\r\n<strong>Entertainment:</strong>Gander Mountain Academy sports complex in Lake Mary, Big Tree Park in Longwood,nearby golf courses in Lake Mary and Longwood, movie theaters in Winter Park.\r\n<strong>Need Help Renting, Buying or Selling a Condominium or Home in Heathrow, FL?</strong>\r\n<strong>Call Us Today!<strong>1-800-975-1475</strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHeathrow is a very small private community of less than 6,000 residents located in Seminole County near Longwood, 19 miles northeast of Orlando and 38 miles southwest of Daytona Beach. It is a census-designated place in unincorporated Seminole County.\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">And while the gated community is comprised mostly of residential units, it is also home to the Heathrow International Business Center office park and headquarters for the American Automobile Association.</p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Twenty-eight separately named and distinct neighborhoods are contained in the area known as Heathrow, which is only about three square miles in size. A three-tier homeowners association oversees the community:</p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">The Heathrow Master Association, headed by a nine-member board of directors, is in charge of enforcing the overall covenants, maintenance of common areas along the main thoroughfare, Heathrow Boulevard, as well as Sawyer Lake Park, other lakes and retention ponds. It is also responsible for maintaining the functionality of the infrastructure and seeing that the community adheres to Florida Statutes regarding homeowners associations.</p>\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Under the Master Association are 12 Neighborhood Associations, each incorporated separately and governed by its own board of directors. With functions similar to the Master Association, they are responsible for common areas within each separate neighborhood or a combination of neighborhoods.</p>\r\nFinally, each of the 28 separate neighborhoods has a committee of three to five representatives elected by residents of those neighborhoods. Committee members, in turn, elect a chairperson, who votes on matters before the Town Advisory Committee and at annual meetings during which the boards of both the Master and Neighborhood Associations are elected. The last, but most local level, is the Neighborhood. Each Neighborhood is required to have a committee comprised of three to five members, all of which are to be elected by the neighborhood residents. As an additional requirement, all of its members must be owners-of-record and residents of the respective neighborhood. The committee chair also arranges and presides over the neighborhood annual meeting.\r\n\r\nThe 28 chairpersons from each neighborhood comprise Heathrows Town Advisory Council, which is also led by a chairperson. The council advises the Master Association board of directors on matters affecting the community and may request action from the Master board of directors on certain items. Town Advisory Council. The TAC meets monthly and also establishes various committees, such as community relations and safety advisory, which meet to discuss issues and report back to the entire council with findings and recommendations.\r\n\r\nFounded in 1985, Heathrow has established a very strict set of covenants for the community. For example, each neighborhood has prescribed architectural characteristics that homeowners must agree to when purchasing a home in Heathrow. The covenants create policies for such things as paint colors, roofing treatments and driveway design. The covenants were established to create a homogeneous look and feel for each neighborhood.\r\n<p lang=\"en-US\">Over the years, Heathrow has attracted a number of notable residents from the sports world, including professional golfers Chris DiMarco, Cliff Kresge, Matt Carroll; baseball players Tim Raines and Tim Raines Jr.; ESPN personality Lee Corso; and NBA player Dwight Howard.</p>', 'Heathrow', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '852-revision-13', '', '', '2013-06-10 07:02:04', '2013-06-10 07:02:04', '', 852, 'http://bricrealty.com/852-revision-13/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
