(1929, 3, '2013-08-07 00:46:54', '2013-08-07 00:46:54', '[property_slideshow]\r\n\r\n[nggallery id=10]\r\n\r\n<strong>Population:</strong>43,243\r\n\r\n<strong>Demographics:</strong>Median age is 34; 79.2 percent white, 9.7 percent black, 15.9 percent Hispanic\r\n<strong>Median household income:</strong>$41,578\r\n<strong>Schools:</strong>Forest City Elementary, Altamonte Elementary, Lake Orienta Elementary, Spring Lake Elementary, Teague Middle School, Lake Brantley High School; private schools are Forest Lake Academy, Forest Lake Education Center, Altamonte Christian School, Saint Mary Magdalen, Pace Brantley Hall School and Annunciation Catholic Academy\r\n<strong>Colleges:</strong>Seminole State College of Florida, Mountain State University, Everglades University, Embry-Riddle Aeronautical University\r\n<strong>Entertainment:</strong>AMC Theater 18-screen cinema, Red, Hot, and Boom Independence Day celebration\r\n\r\n<strong>Need Help Renting, Buying or Selling a Condominium or Home in Altamonte Springs, FL.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Call Us Today!<strong>1-800-975-1475</strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>More About Altamonte Springs:</strong>Located at one of the most heavily traveled intersections in Seminole County, the crossroads of Interstate 4 and State Road 436, Altamonte Springs is a short 15-minute drive from downtown Orlando and about a half hour from Orlando International Airport.\r\n\r\nIn addition to being a well-populated residential area, it is also a major shopping destination as home to the 1.2 million-square-foot Altamonte Mall. The mega mall has about 160 stores where consumers will find a wide array of goods and brand-name retailers such as Abercrombie and Fitch, Banana Republic, Coach Inc. and New York and Company. And while it is the main draw, the mall is by no means the only option for shoppers in the city. Other major retail centers include the Marketplace@Altamonte, West Town Corners, Renaissance Center, Oak Grove Shoppes and Altamonte Crossing. Complementing the retail sector is a business hub that includes offices and commercial space, hotels and a bounty of restaurants.\r\n\r\nMeaning high hill in Spanish, Altamonte is home to more than 43,000 people and it continues to expand. Most recently, the city has focused on creating a 1,375-acre central business district around Cranes Roost Lake. Development has occurred quickly on a 25-acre site known as Uptown Altamonte, a mix of residential units, retail shops, offices and a heavy concentration of restaurants and entertainment venues that form the heart of the new district. Like many of the newer developments in Central Florida Uptown Altamonte is designed to be a self-contained community where families can live, work and play.\r\n\r\nThe outdoor town center is a gathering place with green spaces and a synchronized water fountain, a centerpiece of Cranes Roost Park, which has developed around the lake. It offers recreational space and amenities such as a mile of walkways, restful areas with benches and the Eddie Rose Amphitheater with stadium-style seating and a floating stage. Its just one of several parks in Altamonte Springs. Others include Sunshine Park, Lake Lotus Nature Park, Merrill Park and recreational amenities such as the Lake Orienta public boat ramp and the Lake Brantley Sports Complex.\r\n\r\nThe suburb north of Orlando is a magnet for young families. Of the approximately 20,000 households, it is estimated that about a quarter of them have children under the age of 18. Naturally, the area is served by a number of public and private schools; there are four public elementary schools, a middle school and a high school. A handful of colleges also have branches there including Seminole State College of Florida.\r\n\r\nA 12-screen AMC Theater at the Altamonte Mall is the primary entertainment destination in the city and there are several annual events that are popular. Altamonte Springs in known for having the largest Independence Day celebration in Central Florida. The event, known as Red, Hot, and Boom draws more than 100,000 local residents and visitors and features musical performances by national acts.\r\n\r\n<a name=\"_GoBack\"></a>While automobiles are the main mode of transportation, Altamonte Springs is served by the LYNX transit system of buses, which covers a five-county area (Osceola-Orange-Seminole-Lake-Volusia).', 'Altamonte Springs Florida', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'altamonte-springs-florida', '', '', '2013-08-07 20:42:48', '2013-08-07 20:42:48', '', 0, 'http://bricrealty.com/?post_type=property&#038;p=1929', 0, 'property', '', 0),
(1974, 4, '2013-08-12 21:07:37', '2013-08-12 21:07:37', '<strong>Hiring a Professional Property Manager reduces vacancies and increases income.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>Our Goal is to find Quality Tenants and Help Maintain Your Investment and comply with all Federal, State and Local Laws! <a href=\"http://bricrealty.com/contact-us/\">Contact Us Now</a>to hire our team to manage your Real Estate investments.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Below are all the steps we take to ensure the best property management services to our customers.</strong></em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Tenant Showings</b>- Show prospective tenants vacant units as soon as reasonably possible. Pre-screening process will be conducted via telephone. Maintain a showing schedule and report results to Client. Maintain daily telemarketing efforts for anyone who initially called in. Track tenant lead sources.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Tenant Screening</b>- Conduct thorough tenant screening to include full background check, credit and criminal check, eviction check (at the district magistrate level) at the Tenants expense. Third party company guarantees accuracy and checks all 50 states at three different levels. One of the most thorough in the industry. Approval depends on points system determined by BRIC. All screening is compliant with fair housing laws.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Tenant Placement</b>- Place qualified tenants in vacant units as soon as possible to minimize vacancy. Conduct lease signing to educate tenant on the lease terms, collection procedures, systems of the home, emergency procedures, and other key elements of the lease. We will determine rents based on current market value and consult with Client only if outlined in the Agreement.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Rent Collections</b>- Collect monthly rents from the tenants payable to BRIC, provide receipts for cash payments, and notify owner of any delinquencies with respect to payments of rent. We will serve the proper preliminary notices in the event an eviction is required.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Advertise Properties</b>- Thoroughly advertise units as an ordinary expense in 25 different places; including the newspaper, internet outlets, referral programs, government programs, and other proprietary media.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Accounting</b>- Maintain full, detailed and accurate records and accounts of all receipts and expenditures with respect to the property, which records and accounts shall be available for review by the Property Owner or his representatives, at any reasonable time. We will be responsible for the day to day accounting and banking for client.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Reporting</b>- BRIC has online reporting to all clients. We will send to the Client (Property owner) on or before the fifteenth day of each month, a detailed, itemized statement of all property rent collected and expense receipts incurred during the month.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Maintenance</b>- We have on call 24-hours per day for maintenance emergencies and will make every reasonable effort to protect the property during emergencies. We will responsible for reducing overall maintenance costs, discovering ways to complete repairs more cost-effectively, and ensure tenant is rebilled for any damages caused by them. We will adhere to maintenance limits set by Client during ordinary monthly maintenance.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Maintenance Inspections</b>- We, at the request of the Client, will employ the strategy of monthly or quarterly inspections to ensure the well-being of the properties. We will send maintenance personnel through the property and note any repair issues, missing smoke detectors, plumbing and/or mechanical issues. At the time any issues are found we will either remedy (if within the predetermined limits) or notify the Client via email for remedy and/or notify tenant if they are deemed responsible for such repairs.</em>\r\n\r\n<em><b>Record Management and Backup</b>- It is the goal of the We to keep their systems as paperless as possible. All records are stored electronically with off-site backup to ensure compliance and safeguards against data loss. Records will be made available upon request at any time.</em>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://bricrealty.com/contact-us/\"><strong>Contact Us Now</strong></a> to get started today.', 'More Property Management Information', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'more-property-management-information', '', '', '2013-08-12 21:07:37', '2013-08-12 21:07:37', '', 12, 'http://bricrealty.com/?page_id=1974', 0, 'page', '', 0),
